{"questionId":"33011819","questionHtml":"<p>Hence, or otherwise, show that these roots form a reciprocal pair.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>METHOD 1</strong></p>\n<p>attempts to find their&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>-</mo><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></mrow></mfrac><mo>×</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>+</mo><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>+</mo><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Only award <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em> if the roots are in the form&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>s</mi><mo>±</mo><msqrt><mi>t</mi></msqrt></math>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>+</mo><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></mrow><mrow><msup><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mfenced><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfrac></math> &nbsp; and &nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><msup><mfenced><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>hence the roots form a reciprocal pair&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award as above for attempting to show that&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>+</mo><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>-</mo><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></math>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 2</strong></p>\n<p>considers the product of their roots&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong><em>(M1)</em></strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Only award <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em> if the roots are in the form&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>s</mi><mo>±</mo><msqrt><mi>t</mi></msqrt></math>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>+</mo><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>-</mo><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong><em>A1</em></strong></p>\n<p>hence the roots form a reciprocal pair&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong><em>AG</em></strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 3</strong></p>\n<p>considers&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>c</mi><mi>a</mi></mfrac><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>1</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>the product of roots is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>hence the roots form a reciprocal pair&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"33011819","referenceCode":"24N.3.AHL.TZ0.2aii","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Hence, or otherwise, show that these roots form a reciprocal pair.","paper":"3","level":"HL","questionNumber":"ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.7—Solutions of quadratic equations and inequalities, discriminant and nature of roots","Topic 2—Functions","AHL 2.12—Factor and remainder theorems, sum and product of roots"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}